[ti:Left-Hand Side Answers]
[ar:Taiyang Feng / Suno]
[al:When Winners Stop Winning]
[by:ChatGPT]
[offset:0]

[00:11.20] Two in the morning, blue light on my face
[00:17.24] Another draft open, another line erased
[00:23.68] I rank the winners, I chase the signs
[00:30.28] But every perfect curve breaks down with time

[00:35.91] A glass of red wine beside my screen
[00:42.49] Like a quiet witness to every failed regime
[00:48.73] I ask the market what it hides
[00:54.91] It answers softly through the left-tail side

[01:01.32] They told me, make the logic tighter
[01:05.64] Do not dress weak results in fire
[01:08.20] So I wrote the truth and left it there
[01:13.37] A fragile signal, still worth the care

[01:18.90] When winners stop winning
[01:22.08] I am still searching for the line
[01:25.12] Before the left tail rises
[01:28.08] Before the stars misalign

[01:31.17] When winners stop winning
[01:34.47] I do not run from pain
[01:37.19] I just learn how to lower
[01:40.72] The exposure to the rain

[01:43.29] And if momentum gets tired
[01:46.87] If the bright names start to fall
[01:49.26] I will turn fragility
[01:52.32] Into meaning after all

[02:02.49] Overleaf pages, tables in gray
[02:08.37] Newey-West numbers keeping doubt away
[02:14.26] I used to want the cleanest chart
[02:20.52] Now I want the question with a beating heart

[02:26.88] The wine gets warmer, the night gets thin
[02:32.27] I test the model, then test it again
[02:38.94] Not every signal deserves a name
[02:45.12] Not every backtest survives the flame

[02:51.27] I am not chasing one lucky run
[02:57.35] Or painting alpha where there is none
[03:03.20] If truth is smaller than I planned
[03:08.57] I will still hold it in my hand

[03:15.00] When winners stop winning
[03:18.17] I am searching for the line
[03:21.01] Before the tail risk rises
[03:23.97] Before the stars misalign

[03:27.07] When winners stop winning
[03:30.06] I do not run from pain
[03:32.88] I just learn how to lower
[03:36.21] The exposure to the rain

[03:39.28] And if momentum gets tired
[03:42.58] If the bright names start to fall
[03:45.39] I will turn fragility
[03:48.39] Into meaning after all

[03:56.78] Some dreams live inside a spreadsheet
[04:02.88] Some fears hide inside a test
[04:08.39] Somewhere between a paper draft
[04:14.29] And a half-finished glass of red

[04:21.90] I am young enough to wonder
[04:27.61] Old enough to doubt the game
[04:34.20] But every time the curve breaks down
[04:39.32] I come back and ask again

[04:44.56] When winners stop winning
[04:47.75] I no longer need a sign
[04:50.50] To know that strength can fracture
[04:53.52] At the edge of its own climb

[04:56.81] When winners stop winning
[04:59.70] I will not pretend control
[05:02.50] I will study what is fragile
[05:05.45] And make it part of the whole

[05:08.50] So let momentum get tired
[05:11.29] Let the bright names rise and fall
[05:13.99] I will turn uncertainty
[05:17.65] Into something after all
